cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with biomedical image segmentations using ConvNets. The use of adversarial learning also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also involves the use of unsupervised learning, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The use of different modalities in biomedical imaging could also suggest that it belongs to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the optimization of the domain adaptation module using adversarial loss could suggest that it belongs to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
